{"action": "edit", "code": "def copy_square_to_middle(l: int, s: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes in two integers, l and s, and returns a numpy array of size l x l.\n    It creates a copy of l, and then copies the square area s to the middle black square in the copy of l.\n    \"\"\"\n    copy_l = np.full((l, l), black)\n    mid = l // 2\n    start_x = mid - s // 2\n    end_x = start_x + s\n    start_y = mid - s // 2\n    end_y = start_y + s\n    copy_l[start_x:end_x, start_y:end_y] = teal\n    return copy_l\ndef find_non_black_teal_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.where((input_grid != black) & (input_grid != teal))\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    p = find_non_black_teal_pixels(input_grid)\n    t = find_all_teal_pixels(input_grid)\n    s = find_smallest_square_area(input_grid, t)\n    l = find_smallest_square_area_covering_pixels(input_grid, p)\n    out = copy_square_to_middle(s, l)\n    return out\ndef find_all_teal_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.where(input_grid == teal)\ndef find_smallest_square_area(input_grid: np.ndarray, t: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    min_x, min_y = np.min(t, axis=1)\n    max_x, max_y = np.max(t, axis=1)\n    side = max(max_x - min_x, max_y - min_y)\n    return side ** 2\ndef find_smallest_square_area_covering_pixels(p: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    min_x, min_y = np.min(p, axis=1)\n    max_x, max_y = np.max(p, axis=1)\n    side = max(max_x - min_x, max_y - min_y)\n    return side ** 2", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    p = `find all not black and not teal pixels`(input_grid)\n    t = `find all teal pixels`(input_grid)\n    s = `find the smallest square area that could cover all the pixels in t, return the area in the input_grid`(input_grid, t)\n    l = `find the smallest square area that could cover all the pixels in p, return the area in the input_grid`(input_grid, p)\n    out = `create a copy of l, copy the squar