{"action": "edit", "code": "def copy_square_to_middle(l: np.ndarray, s: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function creates a copy of l and copies the square area s to the middle black square in the copy of l.\n\n    Args:\n    - l: a numpy array representing the input grid\n    - s: an integer representing the area of the smallest rectangle that covers all teal pixels in the input grid\n\n    Returns:\n    - out: a numpy array representing the modified copy of l with the square area s copied to the middle black square\n    \"\"\"\n    rows, cols = np.where(l == black)\n    min_row, max_row = (np.min(rows), np.max(rows))\n    min_col, max_col = (np.min(cols), np.max(cols))\n    mid_row = (min_row + max_row) // 2\n    mid_col = (min_col + max_col) // 2\n    out = l.copy()\n    s_rows, s_cols = np.where(out == s)\n    s_min_row, s_max_row = (np.min(s_rows), np.max(s_rows))\n    s_min_col, s_max_col = (np.min(s_cols), np.max(s_cols))\n    s_width = s_max_col - s_min_col + 1\n    s_height = s_max_row - s_min_row + 1\n    mid_row_start = mid_row - s_height // 2\n    mid_col_start = mid_col - s_width // 2\n    out[mid_row_start:mid_row_start + s_height, mid_col_start:mid_col_start + s_width] = s\n    return out\ndef find_non_black_teal_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    non_black_teal_pixels = np.where((input_grid != black) & (input_grid != teal), 1, 0)\n    return non_black_teal_pixels\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    p = find_non_black_teal_pixels(input_grid)\n    t = find_teal_pixels(input_grid)\n    s = find_smallest_area(input_grid, t)\n    l = find_smallest_covering_area(input_grid, p)\n    out = copy_square_to_middle(s, l)\n    return out\ndef find_teal_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    teal_pixels = np.where(input_grid == teal, 1, 0)\n    return teal_pixels\ndef find_smallest_area(input_grid: np.ndarray, t: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    rows, cols = np.where(t == 1)\n    min_row, max_row = (np.min(rows), np.max(rows))\n    min_col, max_col = (np.min(cols), np.max(cols))\n    area = (max_row - min_row + 1) * (max_col - min_col + 1)\n    return area\ndef find_smallest_covering_area(p: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    rows, cols = np.where(p == 1)\n    min_row, max_row = (np.min(rows), np.max(rows))\n    min_col, max_col = (np.min(cols), np.max(cols))\n    area = (max_row - min_row + 1) * (max_col - min_col + 1)\n    return area", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    p = `find all not black and not teal pixels`(input_grid)\n    t = `find all teal pixels`(input_grid)\n    s = `find the smallest area that could cover all the pixels in t, return the area in the input_grid`(input_grid, t)\n    l = `find the smallest area that could cover all the pixels in p, return the area in the input_grid`(input_grid, p)\n    out = `create a copy of l, copy the square area s to the middle black square in the copy of l`(s, l)\n    return out", "gpt_code": "def copy_square_to_middle(l: np.ndarray, s: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function creates a copy of l and copies the square area s to the middle black square in the copy of l.\n\n    Args:\n    - l: a numpy array representing the input grid\n    - s: an integer representing the area of the smallest rectangle that covers all teal pixels in the input grid\n\n    Returns:\n    - out: a numpy array representing the modified copy of l with the square area s copied to the middle black square\n    \"\"\"\n    rows, cols = np.where(l == black)\n    min_row, max_row = (np.min(rows), np.max(rows))\n    min_col, max_col = (np.min(cols), np.max(cols))\n    mid_row = (min_row + max_row) // 2\n    mid_col = (min_col + max_col) // 2\n    out = l.copy()\n    s_rows, s_cols = np.where(out == s)\n    s_min_row, s_max_row = (np.min(s_rows), np.max(s_rows))\n    s_min_col, s_max_col = (np.min(s_cols), np.max(s_cols))\n    s_width = s_max_col - s_min_col + 1\n    s_height = s_max_row - s_min_row + 1\n    mid_row_start = mid_r